    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n2267" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δέω</span></b>  (2), imp. 3 pl. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δεόντων</span> (better reading <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">διδέντων</span>), ipf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δέον</span>,
          fut. inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δήσειν</span>, aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔδησα, δῆσα</span>, mid. ipf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δέοντο</span>, aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐδήσατο</span>,
          iter. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δησάσκετο</span>, plup. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δέδετο, δέδεντο</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">bind, fasten;</span>
          mid., for oneself, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὅπλα ἀνὰ νῆα</span>,
          ‘making fast their’ tackle, <i><span class="en">Od. 2.430</span></i>;
          metaph., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἡμέτε-</span>
          
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ρον δὲ μένος καὶ χεῖρας ἔδησεν,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 14.73</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc"> ὅς
            τίς μ᾽ ἀ̄θανάτων πεδάᾱͅ καὶ ἔδησε κελεύθου</span> (gen. of
          separation), <i><span class="en">Od. 4.380</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 8.352</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
